
The demo_sessions directory may contain three types of files:

1.  Extension "xls": 
    
    These files are XLWB-sessions which can be loaded into a started XLWB
    by clicking on the menu entry <file> - <load session>.

    A session can be re-executed step by step by hitting <CR> on each input
    region or in one shot by choosing the menu entry <edit> - <reevaluate all>.


2.  Extension "lwb":

    These files contain parsable LWB statements (e.g. procedure definitions).
    They can be read in by entering 

       > read("name.lwb");

    or (XLWB) via the menu entry <file> - <read file>.


3.  Extension "xlr":

    These files contain exemplary resource settings (fonts, colors).




============================================================================
Sessions:
============================================================================


Classical Logic:
  cpc_cnf.xls      :   complexity of conjunctive normal form
  cpc_proofs.xls   :   simple proofs (command cpc::proof, proof display tool)
  cpc_proofoptionsintro.xls :  introduction to the proof display options 
  cpc_simplify.xls :   simplification of classical formulae

  See also:   ipc_intro.xls  
              embeddings.xls

Intuitionistic Logic:
  ipc_intro.xls    :   introduction to intuitionistic logic (compared to cpc)
  
  See also:   embeddings.xls
              ipc_fmls.lwb

Linear Logic:
  ll_intro.xls

  See also:   embeddings.xls


Modal Logics:
  kt5s5.xls        :    equivalence of  KT5 and S5


Non-Monotonic Logics:
  nonmono.xls      :    typical properties (cwa, circ, default).

  See also:   default_extensions_in.lwb


Propositional Linear Time Logic:
  pltl_counter.xls :    a looping 3-bit counter
  pltl_flip.xls    :    a simple 2-bit flip-machine
  pltl_intro.xls   :    introduction to pltl
  pltl_peterson.xls:    Peterson's algorithm for the mutual exclusion problem
  pltl_shift_counter.xls:  3-bit  'shift'-counter (linear feedback register)


Programming:
  programming.xls  :    introduction to the LWB programming language
  
  See also:
    diagram.lwb
    default_extensions_in.lwb


============================================================================
LWB files:
============================================================================


percents.lwb   :    formulae to demonstrate the percentage information

diagram.lwb    :    computation/display of a maximal set of 
                    non-equivalent formulae

default_extensions_in.lwb :  computation of extensions of a default theory




